- First we need to create a repo
    - on GitHub, create the-farm repo with an README.md page
    - git clone https://github.com/billdestein/the-farm.git
- Now add CRA on branch "main"
    - cd the-farm
    - npm init react-app cra
    - cd cra
    - npm install --save gh-pages
    - edit package.json
        - add homepage
            - "homepage": "https://billdestein.github.io/the-farm",
        - add scripts
            - "predeploy": "npm run build"
            - "deploy": "gh-pages -d build"
    - git add .
    - git commit -a -m "Add CRA"
    - git push origin main
- Deploy
    - git branch -d gh-pages
    - git push origin --delete gh-pages
    - git branch gh-pages
    - git checkout gh-pages
    - git push origin gh-pages
    - cd the-farm/cra
    - yarn
    - yarn build
    - yarn deploy
- Test
    - With your browser, go to: https://billdestein.github.io/the-farm/
- Configure a custom domain
    - On Route53 register domain name wade-road-east.com
    - On Route53 create hosted zone wade-road-east.com
    - On Route53 create A record with these IPs
        - 185.199.108.153
        - 185.199.109.153
        - 185.199.110.153
        - 185.199.111.153
    - In github, the-farm, settings
        - set custom domain to "wade-road-east.com"
    - Add CNAME in source tree on branch main
        - edit the-farm/cra/public/CNAME
	- wade-road-east.com
    - In pachage.json, change homepage
         "homepage": "https://wade-road-east.com"        
    - Commit and push
        - git commit -a -m "Add CNAME"
	- git push origin main
      
